*{{IPA|/bluːz/}}
*{{SAMPA|/blu:z/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhmes:English:-uːz|-uːz]]

===Noun===
'''blues'''

# {{plural of|[[blue]]}}
#{{Plurale tantum}} {{colloquial}} A feeling of [[sadness]] or [[depression]].
:*'''Usage note:''' Often preceded by the definite article.
#* '''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: If we had been allowed to sit idle we should all have fallen into the '''blues'''...
#{{Plurale tantum}} {{colloquial}} One's particular life experience, particularly including the hardships one has faced.
#: ''Your blues is just like mine.''
#: ''Your blues are just like mine.''
#{{Plurale tantum}} A musical form, African-American in origin, generally featuring an eight-bar or twelve-bar structure and using the [[blues scale]].
:*'''Usage note:''' Often preceded by the definite article.
#: ''Many great blues musicians came from the Mississippi Delta region.''
#: ''A large portion of modern popular music is influenced by the blues.''
#{{Plurale tantum}} {{cattag|music|always singular}} A musical composition following blues forms.
#: ''My next number is a blues in G.''

